               OSI MODEL
  Open System Interconnection 
It dictates how all network devices will send, receive and interprete data.
 Layer 7 - Application layer
 Layer 6 - Presentation layer
 Layer 5 - Session layer
 Layer 4 - Transport layer
 Layer 3 - Network layer
 Layer 2 - Data link layer
 Layer 1 - Physical layer
 
Application: Users interact with it  directly and its closer to end users eg. browsers uses HTTP/HTTPS
Presentation: Ensures data from one system can be understood by the application on another system,it uses encryption and decryption.
Session: manages a connection between two applications.
Transport: ensures data is delivered end to end between applications reliably and in a correct order,uses TCP/UDP
Network: delivers packets from source to destination device,uses IP address
Datalink: responsible for providing a reliable link between two nodes of the same network,uses mac addresses
Physical: deals with the actual physical transmission of data ovr mediums like cables,fibre,etc 

